76561197987253793,Recommended,514920,28545521,"Posted: 22 December, 2016",all,triplemerc,"This needs work, full stop. Although the game's premise isn't exactly original - being a blend of Stunt Playground, a freeware classic of old, Trackmania, and Clustertruck - it is fairly interesting! You're racing on tracks with obstacles and competition, but being that it's early access, you're dealing with a limited amount of unique assets on the tracks - I hope you like swinging hammers - and you're dealing with a lack of actual real stakes. If you crash, your weightless-feeling car careens off the track and you start again. Your placement relative to your opponents doesn't matter, finish first, finish last, just finish. Considering it seems to want to be physics-based damage-emphasized car game, it's not actually that satisfying or useful to hit opponents, you simply don't have enough control to recoveer properly, and all the cars are flimsy and easily broken. You're better off just staying away from everyone.So it's not bad - it's definitely a good start - but the physics, the tracks, the driving, all need development. I'm excited to see where it goes, and hope that it has a successful development."
