,Recommended,514920,28398413,"Posted: 15 December, 2016",all,Vaxen,"(Review edited on 12/16/2016)Dear devs, as you said, you people are going to develop this game based on the feedback of players. I'm really happy you guys do, because I've got a lot of suggestions to do with this awesome game.This game is really awesome! I want to let you know, as a person who has been playing a lot of racing games for more than 10 years long, that this game, which seems to be in Early Access, is heading in the right direction.The idea of making an arcade racing game with damage physics similar to Next Car Game or BeamNG.drive is an amazing idea! And it works surprisingly well.The driving is pretty decent. The car controls with WASD and brakes with Space. Very simple, very decent.The soundtrack is very enjoyable to listen to. It fits the game well.Graphically, not the best thing I've saw, but honestly, graphics don't matter much if the gameplay is good.The gameplay is VERY addictive. It's so fun to race with many other AI cars with damage physics similar to Next Car Game. It leads to unique crashes, saves and race moments that are totally epic. The tracks are short, but the level design of these tracks is excellent.Crash Wheels is heading to the right direction. However, the only problem of the game is the lack of content.However, there are a lot of ways Crash Wheels can obtain much more content.Devs, consider adding/fixing/improving these:---Add a level creator. Since the main tracks are quite simple, it should also be simple to do a custom level. Have workshop support if it's possible---Add more cars. Having the possibility of driving only one car isn't good. Or at least, make that car customisable. Let players change the colors of the car.---The racing is hard. I'm not sure if there is a drafting system, but if there is, make the drafting more effective. If there's no drafting, add drafting. Or else, it's hard to outrun some AI cars.---If I'm not the first car to reach the finish line, the game still says that I've won. While it might be a reference to Big Rigs, I think it shouldn't say that I've won.---If I try to crash an AI car while driving, I will very easily lose control of my car. While it kind of works, I think the intensity of the loss of control should be toned down a bit.---Add more options, such as a way to change the controls, mute the music or sounds, etc.---Add multiplayer. Both Local and Online multiplayer will work.---Add different camera views, such as a view in the interior of the car, on the hood, etc.---Make the suspension slightly softer. Right now, the suspension is too hard.---Improve the interface of the menus. While there is nothing wrong with simplicity, it would be prettier to have a better looking interface, making the game more professional-looking.---The collision between the sledgehammers and the cars can be quite glitchy. Fix this issue ASAP.In conclusion, you should definitely buy Crash Wheels. It's a very simple game, but it has a bright future and a lot of potential."
